Photoelectrochemical biocatalysis was coupled with the photoelectrochemical regeneration of NADH using the FeOOH/BiVO4/perovskite solar cell tandem configuration with the two-electrode configuration. The reaction medium for the enzymatic reaction consisted of NAD+ (2 mM), M (0.5 mM), α-ketoglutaric acid disodium salt dihydrate (50 mM), (NH4)2SO4 (250 mM), and GDH (40 U) in 3 ml of phosphate buffer (0.1 M, pH 7.5). The l-glutamate production was analyzed by using a 1260 Infinity liquid chromatography system (Agilent Technologies, U.S.A.). TTNGDH, TOFGDH were calculated according to Eqs. (2) and (3), respectively:2TTNGDH=MaximumconcentrationofL-glutamateConcentrationofGDH,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
